  "title": "BUSINESS DEVELOPMENT ASSISTANT ENGINEER",
  "description": "<p>DUTIES & RESPONSIBILITIES:<br />Liaise with customers on RFQs, including obtaining required technical and commercial information and driving the quotation process for new RFQs.</p><p><p>Coordinate RFQ activities with internal functional departments to conduct feasibility studies for newly awarded programs.</p></p><p><p>Source and evaluate new suppliers to meet customer RFQ and project requirements.</p></p><p><p>Prepare and complete New Program Approval documentation to support project launches.</p></p><p><p>Assist Business Development Manager (BDM) / Business Development Executive (BDE) in managing new prototype programs from initiation to launch.</p></p><p><p>Establish prototype project plans and schedules, and manage project budgets accordingly.</p></p><p><p>Act as the key point of contact with customers for enquiries and follow-ups throughout the project lifecycle.</p></p><p><p>Ensure on-time completion and delivery of prototype parts in accordance with customer requirements.</p></p><p><p>Perform any other duties as assigned from time to time.</p></p><p><br />REQUIREMENT:<br />- Diploma in Mechanical Engineering, preferably with specialization or exposure in <strong>Polymer Processing, Plastic Injection Molding, or Mold Making</strong>.</p><p><p>- Minimum <strong>3 years of experience</strong> in <strong>Business Development</strong> within the <strong>Plastic Injection Molding and/or Mold Making industry</strong>.</p></p><p><p>- Good knowledge of <strong>IATF 16949</strong> and <strong>ISO 9001</strong> quality management system requirements.</p></p><p><p>- Proficient in <strong>Microsoft Project</strong> and <strong>Microsoft Excel</strong> for project planning, tracking, and reporting.</p></p><p><p>- Ability to read and interpret <strong>engineering drawings</strong>, including <strong>GD&T (Geometric Dimensioning & Tolerancing)</strong>.</p></p><p></p><p><br /></p>",
